<title>USA: RESEARCH ALERT - Vivus started.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - Vivus started.</headline>
<dateline>MINNEAPOLIS 1997-07-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dain Bosworth Inc said Monday it initiated coverage of Vivus Inc with a strong buy because of the company's growing group of products and an expanding market for treatment of impotency.</p>
<p>-- Analyst Parice Halbert said the potential worldwide market for the company's MUSE product, a needleless drug delivery system to treat impotency, was $1.6 billion to $4.0 billion.</p>
<p>-- Said the company is increasing capacity to meet back orders and an untapped international maket, which could be sizable.</p>
<p>-- Said MUSE product has demonstrated efficacy in a large group.</p>
<p>-- Put a 12-month price target of $45 on the stock.</p>
<p>-- Vivus was up 1-1/2 at 27-3/4 in afternoon trade.</p>
<p>-- ((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk 312-408-8787))</p>
